    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-03-19T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-03-19T19:00:00-05:00" n="792"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d792">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1483a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-19T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 19, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>198. Personal for Kennedy from Welles. The President has asked me to let you know
                    that according to reports which have been reaching us the British are
                    considering making public early this week their plan regarding Palestine. Please
                    take an early occasion informally to offer the suggestion in the right quarter
                    that in view of the international crisis which seems to be shaping up, a short
                    delay in the timing of publication might be of advantage.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
